talent level 10 Upgrade Fearing Gaze
increase health regeneration lost by 3.0
increase mana regeneration lost by 1.5
increase base magic resist reduce by 4%
increase debuff duration by 1.0 seconds
increase attack damage bonus by 22%
increase spellamp bonus by 11%
increase mana cost by 85

add a new modifier Eternal Gaze
Fearing Gaze will become a channeling spell for 1.5 seconds dealing its damage every 0.3 seconds and each instance of damage will do
10% less damage each. It will give it debuff as normal but increasing the mana and health regeneration lost by -0.8 for every tick of
damage and also increasing the chance to fear by 2%. Fearing Gaze will no longer be able to be cast on allys. Esharad will gain a stack
of Eternal Fearing for every fear done, Esharad will gain 0.12 health regeneration and 3 Movespeed max of 35 stacks. At 8 stacks, Eternal
Gaze will gain 0.3 seconds of channel bonus and also reducing the penalty of damage lost every 0.3 seconds by 2%. At 20 stacks, Esharad
will gain 2.5% health and Mana regeneration over the duration of the channel and also increasing the base magic resist lost by -3%. At 28
stacks, Fearing Gaze will be able to be cast on allys again and increasing the bonus damage by 1% and spellamp gain by 0.5% for every 0.2
seconds of Channel, also increase Fearing Gaze damage scaling by 6% and reduce its coldown by 2.


SPELL E Abbysal Pain
Esharad curse the target enemys dealing magical damage every 3.0 seconds over 15 seconds of duration, each tick of damage will also
manaburn the target and further increasing the manaburn by 1.2% 1.6% 2.0% 2.4% 2.8% 3.2% 3.6%, 25% of the manaburn will do magical damage
and also having a small chance to give the lost mana from the target to Esharad every tick of damage. Abbysal Pain cannot be Purge and
it will deal 40% increase damage to target that have less than -20% magic resist and above. this spell will gain 1.7% increase damage and
8.4% manacost increase for every level of Esharad. Also increase Health and also giving coldown reduction as well.

